However, here we still lack something - the virtual operator, which would force those to be cheaper.
It's probably not going to be long before we get there.
That Czech operators are part of the most expensive in Europe, we have already written it in mobil.cz.
The rest was also confirmed by the Czech Telecommunications Office ( T) which warned that the price of SMS messages in our country is among the most expensive in the whole Union.
After the european Commission's last steps in the field of roaming fee regulation, a paradoxical situation is likely to be reached - for some customers of Czech mobile operators SMS sent from abroad will be cheaper than if they are sent from home.
How is it possible that prices in the Czech Republic will remain so high compared to Europe?
The answer is simple, there's a lack of competition that really wants to fight.
We probably find this paradoxical, as we have three mobile networks and their high coverage is more than 100%.
On the contrary, mobile operators like to regret that there is extreme competition in the Czech market.
The President of the Council of the Czech Telecommunications Office, Pavel Dvo-ak, has already stated that there is no longer room in the Czech Republic for any other operator.
